  "body": "In https://github.com/hyperledger/besu/issues/1470 an optional mode was introduced that allowed us to pipe in multiple tests over the stdin pipe. \r\nCurrently a lot of time during fuzzing is spent on setting up the JRE.\r\nHaving an optional flag (--keep or --pipemode or something) would enable us to spin up a besu instance and send state tests to it. This would greatly reduce the overhead of fuzzing. \r\n",
